  "title": "Conversations, Act Two: Contrition for a Cure",
  "summary": "Recovered from her collapse, Doctor Lynae Caiton lingers at the Sandbar as the pilot Jamon makes peace and withdraws, and Keifan eventually bids her a fond farewell. The Jedi pilot Johanna, once banned from this bar and now reformed, joins Lynae and senses through the Force that the punitive implant is killing her. Johanna offers to broker help from the surgeon Doctor Brandis Finian, but demands the truth about Lynae's past first. Lynae confesses that under Malign's orders she aided Fleming in the torture of Finian and his mate Kyrin, yet refuses to apologize for her service as an Imperial officer. Johanna, drawing on her own dark-side guilt over the civilian deaths on Cochran, presses Lynae to admit genuine contrition as the true price of survival, and ultimately offers to take the exiled doctor aboard her ships as a traveling companion to begin reinventing her life.",
